id: pm-hosd
title: Add --with-packages flag to pm init for one-shot package install
description: "After 'pm init', agents must discover that commands like pm calendar/templates live in optional packages and run 'pm install *' separately. Adding --with-packages (or making --defaults install all bundled packages) reduces the cold-start to a single command."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,dogfood,init,packages
created_at: "2026-05-16T16:12:45.824Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T16:12:45.824Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: pm init --with-packages installs all bundled first-party packages automatically; help text mentions the flag; init result includes installed_packages summary; existing pm init behaviour unchanged when flag omitted
parent: pm-rnpb
